ELECTIVE PROFESSIONAL CLIENT DEFINITION
You may wish to elect to opt-up to be treated as a Professional Client (an “Elective Professional Client”) in order for us to supply information to you, following our assessment and approval. Elective Professional Clients lose the benefit of regulatory protections afforded to Retail Clients, so any decision to opt up must be carefully considered.  To fulfil the requirements to opt up to Elective Professional Client status, certain quantitative and qualitative criteria must be fulfilled, potential investors must be aware of and recognise the consequences of the regulatory protections they will lose as a result of opting up and they must agree to being treated as an Elective Professional Client.



Have you worked in the financial sector for at least 1 year in a professional position requiring knowledge of the transactions and/or services sought?

